The roof seems like the back of a prehistoric saurian , the stairs are like the spine of a dinosaur and fish mouths torn open are the balconies .
That is the Casa Batlló by the Catalan architect Antonio Gaudi , in Barcelona .
From the local inhabitants , the house and its organic forms has got the nickname bone house .
Organic forms , wild colors , the unusual use of stone , tile splinters and mosaics , facades that remind one of scales and omnipresent soft lines - all these are typical features of the art nouveau style of Antonio Gaudi .
The facade of the house plays with marvellous lines , gentle colors and textures that remind of nature and living beings .
Before more exact inspection , one does not notice that it is all governed by geometry , rhythm and thought-out order .
In the night the whole facade seems even more plastic , more dramatic and the specific lighting still intensifies the shine of the colors .
The same dynamic lines and twisted forms also dominate the interior of the house .
Wood shaped like waves even copies the window frames , rails , adornment elements of doors , spyholes and strips .
Not the most fabulous bed frame , but the quality of the lying area - therefore the mattress and slats - form the good bed .
These must complement each other harmoniously , however , in order to fulfil the wishes of the specific user .
During the selection many things play a role - the weight , the size , the health state and last but not least also the sex of the sleeper .
Also , the interior in which the mattress and slats have to be stored is just as important .
A typical example ?
In a weekend house which is not regularly heated , latex mattresses are not very suitable , since they need much longer in order to become warm .
In addition they are much heavier than usual polyurethane-mattresses are .
And - they should be turned regularly .
If indeed they do not have enough ventilation channels in the core and also lie on a fixed surface , moisture builds up : it is therefore not impossible for mold to form under it .
